National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: OCHOPEE, FL
Accident Number: MIA85LA223
Date & Time: 08/01/1985, 1030 EDT
Registration: N88AR
Aircraft: Bell 47G-2
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Business
NO DETERMINATION COULD BE MADE AS TO THE NATURE OF THE MAIN ROTOR ASS'Y SEPARATION AS DESCRIBED BY THE PILOT.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: AIRFRAME/COMPONENT/SYSTEM FAILURE/MALFUNCTION Phase of Operation: STANDING - ENGINE(S) OPERATING Findings 1.
(F) ROTOR DRIVE SYSTEM,MAIN GEARBOX/TRANSMISSION - SEPARATION 2.
(C) REASON FOR OCCURRENCE UNDETERMINED ---------- Occurrence #2: ROLL OVER Phase of Operation: STANDING - ENGINE(S) OPERATING Findings 3.
